Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS) provides maximum control over cloud infrastructure while sharing responsibility between Microsoft and customers.

Microsoft manages:

* Physical datacenters
* Hardware
* Networking infrastructure

Customers manage:

* Operating systems
* Applications
* Security configurations
* Data

For example, when using Azure Virtual Machines, Microsoft maintains servers while users patch and configure the operating system.

A real-life use case is migrating legacy enterprise applications without redesigning them.

Another example is organizations requiring custom server configurations.

IaaS provides flexibility while reducing physical infrastructure management.
